            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EGod%20can%20do%20a%20new%20thing!%20He%20told%20Jeremiah%20that%20He%20would%20make%20a%20new%20covenant%20in%20the%20future%20that%20would%20far%20surpass%20the%20old%20one.%20Today%20we%20are%20living%20under%20that%20new%20covenant.%20God%20has%20put%20His%20law%20in%20our%20minds%20and%20written%20it%20on%20our%20hearts.%20He%20has%20forgiven%20our%20wickedness%20and%20will%20remember%20our%20sins%20no%20more%20(Jeremiah%2031%3A34).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EAt%20a%20time%20when%20the%20nation%20of%20Israel%20was%20being%20invaded%2C%20God%20directed%20Jeremiah%20to%20buy%20a%20piece%20of%20property.%20Jeremiah%20purchased%20the%20land%2C%20placed%20the%20deed%20in%20a%20jar%2C%20and%20buried%20it.%20The%20Lord%20promised%20that%20once%20again%20Israel%20would%20return%20to%20the%20land%2C%20and%20the%20deed%20would%20then%20be%20worth%20something.%20Jeremiah%20responded%20to%20the%20Lord%20and%20to%20this%20incredible%20promise%20by%20saying%2C%20%22Nothing%20is%20too%20hard%20for%20you!%22%20(Jeremiah%2032%3A17).%20God%20agreed%20with%20this%20assessment%2C%20saying%2C%20%22I%20am%20the%20Lord%2C%20the%20God%20of%20all%20the%20peoples%20of%20the%20world.%20Is%20anything%20too%20hard%20for%20me%3F%22%20(v.%2027).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EHave%20you%20lost%20all%20hope%3F%20God%20can%20and%20will%20do%20the%20impossible.%20If%20He%20can%20forgive%20your%20sins%20forever%2C%20He%20can%20fix%20your%20problems%20right%20now.%20Place%20your%20confidence%20in%20His%20strong%20covenant.%20Absolutely%20nothing%20is%20too%20difficult%20for%20God!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
